---------------------------------------------------------------------
System:

    melt of 100 chains of 8 atoms.

    Different example subdirectories give examples of different MC
    moves and combinations thereof. The generate/ example uses the
    GENERATE_MOLECULES command to generate a non-equilibrium initial 
    configuration and then uses simple single-particle Monte Carlo 
    moves to relax this system. All other examples use a common input
    configuration file that is already in or very near equilibrium. 

---------------------------------------------------------------------
Usage - Changed directory to example subdirectory and enter:

Serial MC simulation:

    mcSim -e -p param -c commands

Restarting and extending a previous simulation:

    mcSim -e -r restart -c restart.cmd
